[SN]TITLE[SN]
Craig Grant death in Aberdeen: Three charged with murder

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Three men have appeared in court charged with murder after the death of a 26-year-old father in Aberdeen city centre.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Offshore industry worker Craig Grant died early on Friday.
Jonas Marcius, 21, Kiel Hauley, 32, and Adrian Morley, 32, appeared at Aberdeen Sheriff Court where they made no plea and were released on bail.
Earlier, relatives of Mr Grant described him as a "devoted family man".
They said in a statement: "Craig was at his happiest when spending time with his son Owen and wife Fiona.
"He will be sorely missed and his loss will leave a hole in the lives of everyone who knew him."
The incident happened at the Galleria, at the junction of Bon Accord Street and Langstane Place.
